# Project Conventions

## Import Paths

Use path aliases defined in `tsconfig.json`:

```typescript
// ✅ Use alias
import prisma from "@/shared/database/prisma";
import { PersonResponse } from "@/shared/types/person.types";

// ❌ Avoid relative paths
import prisma from "../../shared/database/prisma";
```

## Singleton Pattern

Export singleton instances for controllers, services, and repositories:

```typescript
// ✅ Export singleton
class PersonController { }
export default new PersonController();

// ❌ Don't export class
export class PersonController { }
```

## Async/Await

Always use async/await (never raw promises):

```typescript
// ✅ Use async/await
async function getData() {
  const result = await repository.findAll();
  return result;
}

// ❌ Avoid .then()
function getData() {
  return repository.findAll().then(result => result);
}
```

## Error Messages

Use descriptive, user-friendly error messages:

```typescript
// ✅ Clear and specific
throw new Error("Person with name 'John' already exists");
throw new Error("Cannot marry a person to themselves");

// ❌ Vague
throw new Error("Invalid input");
throw new Error("Error");
```

## Response Structure

All API responses follow this structure:

```typescript
// Success
{
  success: true,
  data: any,
  message?: string,
  count?: number
}

// Error
{
  success: false,
  error: string,
  message: string
}
```

## Database Access

- Only repositories access Prisma
- Services call repositories
- Controllers call services
- No layer should skip levels

## File Organization

```
src/
├── features/          # Feature modules
│   ├── persons/
│   └── marriage/
├── shared/           # Shared code
│   ├── database/     # Prisma client
│   └── types/        # Type definitions
└── app.ts           # Application entry
```
